  "prompt": "I've only heard one song by Jackson Browne which I totally loved! 'Late for the sky'! Can anyone recommend me more Jackson Browne songs? Even albums?",
  "response": "If you loved \"Late for the Sky,\" you'll likely enjoy more of Jackson Browne's work! Here are some recommended songs and albums that showcase his poignant songwriting and evocative melodies:\n\n### Recommended Songs:\n1. **\"Doctor My Eyes\"** - A classic track that highlights Browne's signature sound.\n2. **\"Running on Empty\"** - An upbeat song that captures the essence of life on the road.\n3. **\"The Pretender\"** - A heartfelt ballad with a reflective message.\n4. **\"Take It Easy\"** - Co-written with Glenn Frey, this song has a laid-back vibe.\n5. **\"Fountain of Sorrow\"** - Another beautiful, introspective track with emotional depth.\n6. **\"Before the Deluge\"** - A powerful song that discusses themes of change and impermanence.\n7. **\"Somebody's Baby\"** - A catchy tune featured in the film *Fast Times at Ridgemont High*.\n\n### Recommended Albums:\n1. **\"Late for the Sky\"** (1974) - Since you love that song, this entire album is worth listening to.\n2. **\"Jackson Browne\"** (1972) - His self-titled debut album, featuring early classics like \"Doctor My Eyes.\"\n3. **\"For Everyman\"** (1973) - Known for its introspective themes and great songwriting.\n4. **\"Running on Empty\"** (1977) - A live album that captures the energy of his performances along with studio tracks.\n5. **\"The Pretender\"** (1976) - This album includes some of his most notable songs.\n\nExploring these songs and albums should give you a great sense of Jackson Browne's style and depth as a musician. Enjoy!",
